{{italic title}} '''''Does the World Hate the United States?''''' is a 2005 book, edited by [[Andrea C. Nakaya]]. It is in the [[At Issue series]] of American textbooks, intended according to the publisher for grades 10 to 12+.<ref>{{cite book|author=Alexander Stephan|title=The Americanization of Europe: Culture, Diplomacy, and Anti-Americanism After 1945|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=sgCqwXmGxNYC&pg=PA369|year=2006|publisher=Berghahn Books|isbn=978-1-84545-085-4|page=369}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://solutions.cengage.com/greenhaven/|title=Greenhaven Press - Cengage Learning|accessdate=27 August 2015}}</ref>
The book presents selections of viewpoints on questions about [[anti-Americanism]], its extent and causes in relationship to [[Foreign relations of the United States|its foreign policies]] and [[popular culture]], and whether it is rooted in [[jealousy]]. It was published by [[Greenhaven Press]] ([[Farmington Hills]]) in 2005 as a 139-page hardcover ({{ISBN|0-7377-2368-8}}) and paperback ({{ISBN|0-7377-2369-6}}).
