'''Jakob Jud''' [ju:t] (12 January 1882 in [[Wängi]], Kanton [[Thurgau]] &ndash; 15 June 1952 in [[Seelisberg]], Kanton [[Canton of Uri|Uri]]) was a [[Swiss people|Swiss]] [[Romance languages|Romance]] [[linguistics|linguist]] ([[wikt:Romanist#Noun|Romanist]]).
From 1922 to 1950 he taught classes in Romance philology and Old French literature at the [[University of Zürich]].<ref>[http://www.hls-dhs-dss.ch/textes/d/D42192.php Jud, Jakob] Historischen Lexikon der Schweiz</ref> With [[Karl Jaberg]], he was the author of ''Sprach- und Sachatlas Italiens und der Südschweiz'' (8 volumes, 1928–40).<ref>[http://www.worldcat.org/title/sprach-und-sachatlas-italiens-und-der-sudschweiz/oclc/12210881 Sprach- und Sachatlas Italiens und der Südschweiz] OCLC WorldCat</ref> In 1936, with Arnald Steiger, he founded the magazine ''Vox Romanica''.<ref>[https://www.jstor.org/stable/27939841?seq=1#page_scan_tab_contents Vox romanica] Romanische Forschungen &ndash; 100. Bd., H. 1/3, 1988</ref> == References == {{reflist}}
