{{Infobox person | name = | image = | imagesize = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = 27 January 1935 | birth_place = [[Bayonne]] | death_date = {{Death date and age|df=yes|2009|08|10|1935|01|27}} | death_place = Athens | othername = | occupation = Historian of art | years_active = | spouse = | signature = }}
'''Léon Pressouyre''' (27 January 1935 - 10 August 2009) was a French historian of [[medieval art]].
An [[Agrégation in France|agrégé of history]], he was a member of the [[École française de Rome]] (1964–1966). Attached then maître de recherches at the [[Centre National de la Recherche Scientifique]], he was professor of art history and archaeology of the Middle Ages at the University Paris I from 1980 to 1997.
He was permanent advisor of the International Council on Monuments and Sites of the [[UNESCO]] (1980–2005).
Léon Pressouyre was a member of the [[Société des Antiquaires de France]].
